ozwell.s1: The two notes are very similar. They both describe the case of a 25-year-old male patient with a history of a painless bony mass on the right arm, diagnosed with grade II chondrosarcoma. Both notes mention the patient's past medical history of Ollier's disease, the physical examination findings, radiographic examination results, and the treatment plan involving limb-salvage surgery with prosthetic replacement. The follow-up and postoperative recovery details are also consistent between the two notes.
